Sentencing hearing proceeded. Court finds the State has complied with the victim rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Jeremy O., Tonya H., Paul H., and Brian F. 

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 25 YEARS, consecutive to COUNT 2, concurrent with COUNT 3; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS.  

As to COUNT 2-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 25 YEARS, consecutive to COUNTS 1 & 3; credit for 145 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS.  

As to COUNT 3-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 25 YEARS, consecutive to COUNT 2, concurrent with COUNT 1; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

